.TH "LIGHTNING-DAEMON" 1 "Jun 2026" "lightning 0.7.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-daemon \- lightningd lifecycle management
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning daemon
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning daemon — lightningd lifecycle management.

All sub-commands accept --user (default) or --system.

lifecycle:
  start    — bring up lightningd (background)
  run      — foreground (for launchd / systemd)
  stop     — graceful shutdown
  restart  — stop + start
  status   — health check
  monitor  — tail the daemon log

setup:
  install  — install lightningd (brew|apk|source|rpk|podman)
  enable   — install + start launchd/systemd unit
  disable  — stop service and remove unit
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning daemon <subcommand> [args]

   Lifecycle of the underlying clightningd process.
   All sub-commands accept --user (default) or --system.

   lifecycle:
     start [--user|--system]    bring up lightningd (background)
     run                         foreground (for launchd / systemd)
     stop [--user|--system]     graceful shutdown
     restart [--user|--system]  stop + start
     status [--user|--system]   health check
     monitor [--user|--system]  tail the daemon log

   setup:
     install [--from <src>]     install lightningd (brew|apt|apk|source)
     enable [--user|--system]   install + start launchd/systemd unit
     disable [--user|--system]  stop service and remove unit

   see 'lightning daemon help <subcommand>' for detailed usage.
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.